      "message": "#fuchsia:\n\n\u003cscottmg\u003e when i call zx_object_get_info ZX_INFO_PROCESS_THREADS with a (e.g.) a zero sized buffer, it always returns ZX_OK, never ZX_ERR_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL (which i would sort of expect if avail \u003e actual)\n\u003cscottmg\u003e is that intentional behaviour, or should i file a bug about that?\n\u003c•swetland\u003e that is intentional\n\u003c•swetland\u003e it returns as many threads as it can in the provided buffer\n\u003c•swetland\u003e it tells you how many it *could* return at that moment in avail\n\nZX_ERR_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL seems to only be used for single-item return calls. /shrug",
